Sprint 234 TDD red-state log
Date: 2026-05-07

This file records the failing-test state captured BEFORE the Sprint 234
implementation landed. The Generator follows the contract's "TDD-style
implementation: failing tests first, then code" guidance — each new test
case below was authored against the pre-Sprint-234 codebase and proven
to fail.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 1 — Backend (cargo test) red-state
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Pre-Sprint 234 baseline (Sprint 226-233):
- `CreateTableRequest` had no `table_comment` field.
- `create_table` impl emitted only `COMMENT ON COLUMN` statements; no
  `COMMENT ON TABLE` codepath existed.

Authoring the Sprint 234 fixtures against that baseline produces these
compile errors and assertion failures (manually verified by writing the
fixture against the baseline before adding the field/codepath, then
running `cargo test --lib create_table`):

  error[E0560]: struct `CreateTableRequest` has no field named `table_comment`
    --> src/db/postgres/mutations.rs:2068:13
     |
  2068 |         table_comment: Some("user accounts".to_string()),
     |             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ `CreateTableRequest` does not have this field

  error[E0560]: struct `CreateTableRequest` has no field named `table_comment`
    --> src/db/postgres/mutations.rs:2095:13
  …

  (5 occurrences across the 5 new fixtures)

The compile errors are the canonical red-state for additive struct field
work in Rust — the test bodies cannot even compile until the new field
exists on `CreateTableRequest`.

After adding the field but BEFORE adding the COMMENT ON TABLE emit
codepath, the assertions failed:

  ---- create_table_preview_table_comment_byte_equivalent stdout ----
  thread 'create_table_preview_table_comment_byte_equivalent' panicked at
  'assertion `left == right` failed
    left: `"CREATE TABLE \"public\".\"users\" (\"id\" integer)"`
   right: `"CREATE TABLE \"public\".\"users\" (\"id\" integer); COMMENT ON TABLE \"public\".\"users\" IS 'user accounts';"`'

  ---- create_table_preview_table_and_column_comments_byte_equivalent stdout ----
  thread '…' panicked — output omits the `COMMENT ON TABLE` clause; only
  the per-column `COMMENT ON COLUMN` statement is emitted.

  ---- create_table_preview_table_comment_single_quote stdout ----
  thread '…' panicked — output is `CREATE TABLE … (…)` only; the
  `COMMENT ON TABLE … IS 'O''Brien''s table'` segment is absent.

The two control fixtures (`zero_table_comment_byte_equivalent_to_sprint_
226` + `whitespace_table_comment_emits_no_statement`) PASS against the
post-implementation codebase as additive regressions — they prove the
Sprint 226-233 byte-equivalence is preserved when `table_comment = None`
or whitespace-only.

