SECTION 2 — Frontend (vitest) red-state
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Pre-Sprint 234 baseline (Sprint 226-233):
- `usePostgresTypes` returned only `{ types, loading, error, reload }`.
  No `typesByName: Map<string, string>` field.
- `CreateTableTypeCombobox` had no `typeKindMap` prop.
- `CreateTableDialog` rendered the schema picker INSIDE the header.
- No "Table comment" input.
- No `(N)` count badges on tab triggers.
- No ↑/↓ reorder buttons on row repeaters.
- Empty-state strings used the verbose Sprint 227-229 form.

The Sprint 234 vitest cases authored against that baseline fail with:

  ● usePostgresTypes (Sprint 234) › surfaces a typesByName map matching
    the live PostgresTypeInfo entries
    expect(received).toBeInstanceOf(Map)
    Received: undefined        ← `result.current.typesByName` is undefined

  ● CreateTableTypeCombobox (Sprint 234) › renders a blue dot prefix for
    enum-typed options when typeKindMap supplies enum
    expect(received).toBeInTheDocument()
    Received: null             ← no `[data-testid="type-kind-dot-…"]` in DOM

  ● CreateTableDialog (Sprint 234) › renders the target schema dropdown
    in the body, not in the header (AC-234-07)
    expect(headerEl).not.toContainElement(schemaCombobox)
    The combobox IS inside the header                       ← header still has it

  ● CreateTableDialog (Sprint 234) › renders a Table comment input above
    the tabs (AC-234-05)
    Unable to find a label "Table comment" in the document  ← input absent

  ● CreateTableDialog (Sprint 234) › shows (N) count badge next to
    Keys / Indexes / Foreign Keys tab labels (AC-234-01)
    Unable to find a tab with text "Keys (1)"               ← no badge

  ● CreateTableDialog (Sprint 234) › Move column up/down buttons reorder
    rows in place and disable at boundaries (AC-234-03)
    Unable to find a button "Move column down"              ← no reorder ui

  ● CreateTableDialog (Sprint 234) › surfaces empty-state message when
    no named column exists (AC-234-02)
    Expected text "Add named columns in the Columns tab to use this picker."
    Found "Add a column with a name to choose primary key columns"

  ● IndexesTabBody (Sprint 234) › renders Move up/down buttons disabled
    at first and last index row
    Unable to find a button "Move index up"                 ← no reorder ui

These are the targeted red-states. Implementation lands the code that
turns each red into green.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 3 — Implementation order (red→green sequence)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. Backend `CreateTableRequest.table_comment` + `COMMENT ON TABLE` emit
   → resolves all 5 cargo red-states.
2. `usePostgresTypes` `typesByName` Map field
   → resolves the 2 hook red-states.
3. `CreateTableTypeCombobox` `typeKindMap` prop + dot render
   → resolves the 4 combobox red-states.
4. `CreateTableDialog/Header.tsx` strip schema picker
   + `CreateTableDialog.tsx` body restructure (schema picker above
   table name input + table comment input + tab badges + reorder
   buttons + empty-state message)
   → resolves the 6 dialog red-states.
5. `IndexesTabBody.tsx` reorder buttons + empty-state message
   → resolves the 2 IndexesTabBody red-states.

After Step 5 every red turns green. Verification command sweep
(vitest run + tsc --noEmit + lint + cargo test + cargo clippy + cargo
fmt --check + pnpm build) confirms end-to-end.
